HEADWORD: Ossific
<hw>Os*sif"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>os</ets>,
<ets>ossis</ets>, bone + <ets>facere</ets> to make: cf. F.
<ets>ossifique</ets>. See <er>Fact</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of
producing bone; having the power to change cartilage or other tissue
into bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ossification</ent>⟦br⟧
